Air Arabia, Qatar Electricity: Persian Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-10-04T02:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/air-arabia-qatar-electricity-persian-gulf-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Persian Gulf stock markets. Symbols are in parentheses and
prices are from the last close.  Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  dropped 1.6 percent to the lowest
since March 7. Saudi Arabia’s  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  lost 1.4
percent and Abu Dhabi’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  decreased 0.7 percent.  Air Arabia PJSC (AIRARABI UH): The  Middle East ’s biggest
low-cost airline is “favored” by EFG-Hermes Holding SAE, the
bank said in a note dated Oct. 3, citing revenues and “strong”
load factors. EFG-Hermes has a “buy” recommendation on the
stock. The shares decreased 0.8 percent to 61.9 fils.  Qatar Electricity & Water Co. (QEWS)  : The second-largest
publicly traded utility in the Middle East by market
capitalization is EFG-Hermes’ top pick in the utilities
subsector, the bank said yesterday, citing the company’s
dividend yields, revenue and “cash flow visibility.” The
shares declined 0.3 percent to 136.6 riyals.  Rabigh Refining & Petrochemicals Co. (PETROR)  : The Saudi
Arabian fuel producer aims to gain market share in  Europe  by
benefitting from access to low-cost natural gas and by expanding
output, Chief Executive Officer Ziad al-Labban said. The shares
retreated 1 percent 24.85 riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
